  "texts": [
    "An extreme example illustrates this: if a testbench reports a \"pass\" for any DUT, its Eval1 pass rate would be 100%.",
    "Therefore, Eval2 is required for a comprehensive assessment of testbenches.",
    "Eval2 is a coverage-based criterion and is deemed as pass when its ratio is over 80% in this work, as discussed in Section 4.",
    "To analyze the detailed coverage distribution of generated testbenches, the ones passing Eval1 from 1560 tasks (156×10 samples) were selected and the distribution of their Eval2 coverage is presented in Fig.5.",
    "Compared with the baseline, Eval2 coverage of AutoBench is more concentrated on the right side, which means AutoBench is more capable of detecting errors in the DUTs than the baseline."
  ],
